On the surface this appears rational but it doesn't deal with the problem. Much Uranium and Plutonium goes 'missing' every year. Terrorism is a longterm problem that will only escalate in enormity if you ignore it by sticking your head in the sand. Uranium is not the rarest of elements to obtain, reactor technology is so widespread and terrorists so well financed it is inevitable they will have the bomb some day. Who are they? Anyone who hates the west enough to nuke us. Plenty of fanatical countries to choose from there. I was writing about this long before September 11th by the way.<br>
They WILL get the means to nuke the west hard eventually. Critics of nuclear power will reply &quot;We'll, any sane person would try and put that day off as long as possible.&quot;<br>
Then what?<br>
This &quot;hide under the bedcovers and pretend the nuclear threat doesn't exist&quot; policy might work for a time but it causes us to think there is no problem. We leave it to the Government to try and police the entire World and listen via satellite and earthquake devices for the telltale vibration of an illegal weapons test. We don't even know who has the bomb or how many countries are working on it. Wasn't India and Pakistan a surprise! Ignoring the problem in the way we are causes me great concern. For while we reduce our stockpiles, ban research into fusion technology and make futile attempts to stop others many countries are just biding their time. Gathering up information and building up contacts. Many no doubt already have the bomb but are waiting until the ideal moment when they can do maximum carnage. Perhaps after bombs have been hidden in every major US city. We could be trading our childrens security for our own. After decades of peace they will be startled like docile newly born sheep at seeing the end of their World. The survivors wandering through the ruins of their shopping malls and high rises.<br>
Like I said, I wrote of this long before September 11th and was laughed at. Nobody is laughing now. I think it's time we pulled our heads out of the sand. The nuclear genie is not going away. It cannot be bottled again. It cannot be uninvented. It can be better understood. Therein lies our one possible salvation for hate is also immortal. It can never be removed completely and so the danger will always exist. The answer to the problem is not to turn away from it but face it. Nothing is more frightening than the unknown and despite over half a century of knowing this technology we are still unfamiliar with it. Nuclear science remains in it's infancy.<br>
We should increase research into this cutting edge state of the art science. Then we can better understand and defend ourselves from it aswell as find peaceful purposes to use it for. Remember that all technology is a two edged sword. Fire and Electricity have killed untold thousands but where would we be without them. Living in caves eating raw meat. Don't laugh. Banning nuclear power is the same as turning our backs on those turning points in civilisation for they were also seen as evil uncontrollable forces of nature at one time.<br>
We can now harness the power of the sun. Do we take this technology by the throat and wring it's secrets free or ignore it at our peril and pray that the terrorists don't aquire this 40's technology and destroy us.<br>
<br>
Nuclear power can give us the stars.    <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
